Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.62,0:00:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. Hello. Thank you.\NSome of you have been asking if we have a bookstore,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.34,0:00:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you go right out here,\Nyou'll see the sign on the door that says bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, it's off here to the left, my left, your right, whatever.\NAnyway, it's right up there. It says bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.77,0:00:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we do have a bookstore, and all the material are available there.\NMust be time for a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.28,0:00:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll have to tell you the black mamba story.\NDid I ever tell you the black mamba story?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.10,0:01:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A friend of mine that liked to collect exotic animals,\Nhe had a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a guard dog, and when he let it out of the car,\Nhe would say to me, stand still, don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.91,0:01:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so he had a, as I say, he liked exotic animals.\NPeople get to throw all those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.24,0:01:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So he had a black mamba.\NAnd the black mamba lived in a big cage, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.58,0:01:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And those were the days when LSD was around, you know.\NSo anyway, this friend of mine did LSD,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.86,0:01:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden, the black mamba starts talking to him.\NAnd the black mamba says, I'm friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.58,0:01:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to keep me locked in this cage.\NIf you let me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.08,0:02:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be very gentle with you.\NSo, no, no, he said, I'm not letting you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.33,0:02:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The black mamba gets very disappointed and says,\Nwell, you don't even trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.41,0:02:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what kind of a friend are you and all this kind of stuff?\NSo he thinks about it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So he calls a friend of his.\NHe tells the friend of his, this black mamba says, it's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.51,0:02:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can let me out.\NWhat should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.20,0:02:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And this friend of him says, don't believe me, he's lying.\NWhere's the light?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the projection?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.41,0:02:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThat's a true story, a true story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Good friend of mine.\NVery good friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.90,0:02:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo we see that one teaching of the Buddha is that you should be grateful that you're born a human
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.18,0:03:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the karmic opportunity to undo negative karma,\Nand acquire good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So being born a human is rare, fortunate, and the consequence of good karma.\NSo instead of cursing your human existence, say, oh, why was I born, and all that kind of stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.36,0:03:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, well, this is a world of great opportunity because I can choose to condemn\Nor I can choose to forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.87,0:03:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that we have freedom of choice then means we can understand that there's a lot\Nof good and bad in this world, and we can undo the negative and gain positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the best spiritual advice is to be kind and loving towards all of life and\Nall of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.86,0:04:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if you're going to be beheaded, you say to the headsman, thank you so much for\Ndoing a very good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.34,0:04:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And bless him at his work.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.28,0:04:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's another viewpoint.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.90,0:04:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is a trap of illusion.\NTherefore, salvation depends on non-attachment to its linear and emotional qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.85,0:04:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's only at 230.\NThe world is a trap of illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.44,0:04:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's sort of a negative view of it, isn't it?\NIt's not really a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one who's trapped is your belief that you're trapped.\NActually, you're completely free, and you don't have to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.05,0:04:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo that's the trap of illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.63,0:04:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see that from the wolf in sheep's clothing and what you see depends on what\Nyou project into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.48,0:05:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the perceived world is the result of the projection of human consciousness and therefore\Nakin to a Rorschach card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.87,0:05:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As a psychiatrist, that's the way I used to think of it very often.\NOne person would see everything as hateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.78,0:05:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,another person would see everybody as trustable, and so people seem to project onto the world\Ntheir own inner state of mind. So how can you transcend this situation where you're either
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.75,0:05:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,trapped in your own illusions? How do you know that you're perceiving reality at all?\NAnd I just got through telling you about the chimpanzee and the white tiger and the friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.35,0:05:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,lion. They look friendly and trustable, and each one of them ended up savaging or killing a person.\NSo how can you find out what the truth of it is? Frankly, without calibrating it, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We hate to tell you that, but that's a fact.\NYeah, the true reality of the world is unknowable only to the ego, but to the spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's quite knowable. The world is really a rare opportunity for maximum spiritual growth,\Nso the best thing to do is be thankful and give thanks to the Lord for this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.02,0:06:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because in this lifetime I can undo the negative and gain the positive. The world is a rare\Nopportunity for maximum spiritual growth. Undo the bad and the earning of the new. That calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at 510.\Nthat's a very trustable teaching. 510 is a very trustable teaching then. Let's move on to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.37,0:07:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,next slide. The world is, one of the last books we published, we give about 40 different ways of\Nseeing the world, I think 35 or 40, but we didn't calibrate any of them. So I thought it'd be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting to go back and pick up a number of them that tend to be prevailing and calibrate\Nthem. So although some of them are stated in the book, there are no calibrations given in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it just says there's, you know, at least 35 different ways that you can choose to view the\Nworld. So I thought it would be interesting then to calibrate them. So to say the world is a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.25,0:07:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,meaningless kaleidoscope of sensations, and that all meaning is fairly projection, calibrates only\Nat 250. In other words, it's true to a certain extent, it's kaleidoscopic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.83,0:08:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And sensations, the fact that it's meaningless means that all meaning is projected onto the\Nworld by yourself. In and of itself, it lacks any intrinsic meaning. This is also true only
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.14,0:08:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on a certain level. On another level, it is not true. The world is not really essentially\Nmeaningless unless you understand by what we mean by meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.33,0:08:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All meaning is something you impose upon the world. The world in and of itself\Nhas no intrinsic meaning to the average mind. The more advanced mind, with the meaning of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.31,0:08:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is the presence of divinity as the perfection of all that is. But by that time, a person is\Nvery advanced to see that the world is an expression of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:09:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is the theatrical stage for the comedy of the absurd.\NThis is a common presumption. Often it's part of humor, you know. Absurdity is part of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.50,0:09:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The world and human life are the consequence of the fall of Adam and Eve due to disobedience\Nand succumbing to the temptation of curiosity. Life is therefore penitential
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.83,0:09:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for the absurd. The world is the theatrical stage for the comedy of the absurd. The world is the\Noriginal sin. Calibrates at 190. So that's a certain interpretation then of the Bible, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.94,0:09:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That Eve fell for the temptation of the serpent and pulled Adam down with her. Did she do that?\NOh, blame it on Eve. No, blame it on the serpent. Blame it on the serpent. Blame it on Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.15,0:10:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave the guys alone, you know.\NIt's interpreted, interpreted then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as punishment for disobedience.\NI have never agreed with that viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought that intrinsic to consciousness\Nis the nature of human consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Within everyone's consciousness\Nis really the consciousness of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.74,0:10:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you believe anything is that within you,\Nwithout its layers of sophistication,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.44,0:10:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is still actually basically the consciousness of the child.\NNot different than the child's, but just not elaborated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.98,0:10:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So basic to everyone within oneself\Nis there's still the innate, pure consciousness of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:11:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So my interpretation of that story\Nis that the serpent was aware
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.06,0:11:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that the consciousness of the child\Nstill resided in Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.13,0:11:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he appealed not to her disobedience,\Nbut to her curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me, I won't hurt you.\NYou can trust me, you can trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.65,0:11:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I feel that she was the victim\Nof her own innocence, inner innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.14,0:11:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of her innocence, she did not suspect\Nthat anything other than innocence prevailed anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I saw it like she was sinless.\NI see it as sinless, like a sophistication,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.11,0:11:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like a being aware.\NThat the innermost layer of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.96,0:11:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is childhood innocence prevails in everyone.\NAnd it can be manipulated by evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.34,0:11:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that by Bernie Merkhardt.\NWhat's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.46,0:12:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Bernie, the super billionaire ripoff?\NMadoff, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.23,0:12:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Mr. Madoff.\NMadoff with what, $500 billion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.80,0:12:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting people's money, see?\NSo how did they get away with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.50,0:12:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because within each one, there was the child\Nthat wants to believe in the goodness of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.21,0:12:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and is trusting.\NAnd the child within us is trusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to be careful.\NIt's not just the evil of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.78,0:12:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but the innocent trustingness within our own inner child.\NSo it's our own inner child that gets us into trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a good deal of the time.\NFirst of all, the inner child is curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.91,0:12:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, it doesn't know anything about evil yet,\Nhasn't lived long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, it doesn't think to be on guard.\NIt would not even guess that a good friend
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.82,0:13:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,would rip you off for millions of dollars.\NIt would not suspect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So some of us have a hard time getting over\Nthat intrinsic innocence of the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.20,0:13:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have the tendency to be overly trusting\Nand trust others who are not really trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.87,0:13:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the world?\NThe world and humanity were created by God
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.71,0:13:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and are therefore divinely inspired and intrinsically holy.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.36,0:13:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That is certainly a more positive view of God.\NThan viewing creation as punishment for original sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd rather pick this view.\NPlus the caliber is a lot higher than the original one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.08,0:14:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,545 is a lot better than 190 or whatever the other one.\NThe world and humanity were created by God
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.68,0:14:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore divinely inspired and intrinsically holy.\NWhen the ego subsides,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.42,0:14:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic beauty and purposefulness\Nand perfection and holiness of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth like a radiance.\NIt shines forth from the world itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you witness it.\NIt's like the world is illuminated
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.83,0:14:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the energy of luminosity\Nshines out of everything that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.22,0:14:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you first perceive of it,\Nyou have to pull your car over to the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.76,0:14:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you saw that day, right?\NAnd I remember when I first saw it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.22,0:14:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It stopped everything.\NAnd I really wasn't able to function for a period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.21,0:15:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The intrinsic beauty and perfection of all that exists\Nshines forth because all that exists is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.22,0:15:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists.\NThere's nothing that exists that is not God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.37,0:15:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But the divinity of his essence does not shine forth\Nbecause we tend to reject onto it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.31,0:15:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,our own perceptions and belief systems.\NOur own perceptions about the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.98,0:15:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A more limited view then.\NThe world is merely a physical product
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.72,0:15:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the physical universe.\NThis is the pedestrian scientific viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.57,0:15:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are professional atheists.\NSome of them I suppose are humorous too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're professional atheists\Nand they poo-poo anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.13,0:15:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,any other depiction of the universe\Nthat the world is merely a physical product
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.18,0:15:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the physical universe.\NThat the world is merely a physical product
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.92,0:15:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the physical universe.\NAnd God is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.42,0:15:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,God is an illusion.\NAnd the professional atheist feels sorry for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.98,0:16:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that comedian that comes out\Nand ridicules God all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.08,0:16:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember his name, Gabe.\NWhat's his name, do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.45,0:16:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.39,0:16:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That world's an illusion.\NYou think you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.85,0:16:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NPhilmar?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil.\NBillmar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Billmaher.\NBillmaher.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.32,0:16:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Billmaher.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.60,0:16:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Billmaher.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a funny guy.\NBut, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.50,0:16:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he likes to ridicule anything\Nthat is not just strictly
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.04,0:16:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the most pedestrian physical view\Nof the world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.20,0:16:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So his view of the world,\Nhis view of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.95,0:16:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to do this,\Nhis view of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:17:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the view that he presents,\NI have permission to not calculate this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.09,0:17:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 190 resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the view that he pervades to the world\Nis 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.32,0:17:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's just a physical phenomena\Nand that God is just an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's quite a big difference\Nbetween seeing the world at 545
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.80,0:17:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing the world as pedestrian materialism.\NSo this is what we call, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the materialistic view of the world,\Nmechanical materialistic, 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.84,0:17:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Next we have life and humanity\Nare purely accidental products
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.98,0:17:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of Darwinian biologic evolution.\NSo this view that he pervades,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,projects,\Nand this particular view
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.65,0:18:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is called mechanistic reductionism.\NIt calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.95,0:18:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a physical universe.\NIt's a physical universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.15,0:18:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a physical universe.\NIt's nothing but a product of physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.75,0:18:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an expression of physicality.\NSo that's Darwinian mechanistic reductionism.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.14,0:18:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the schools,\Nwe have now a conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.82,0:18:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,between the different explanations of evolution,\Nbetween creationism, creationism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.61,0:18:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and Darwinian, Darwinian biologic evolution.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.57,0:18:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we have a more,\Na more sophisticated view.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.05,0:18:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Survival is due to natural selection\Nby the survival of the fittest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectually, that's true.\NThe survival of the fittest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.28,0:18:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you got bigger teeth than the rabbit,\Nyou survive and the rabbit does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.54,0:19:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSome of these are such comical views.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.19,0:19:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I just love them.\NThe world and the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,are merely passing illusions\Ncreated by the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.99,0:19:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep itself separate from God.\N220.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.89,0:19:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, 220.\NIn other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.07,0:19:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's sort of true,\Nbut not really totally true
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.19,0:19:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or overwhelmingly true.\NBut this is sort of a spinoff
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from some spiritual teachings.\NThe world and the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.53,0:19:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are merely passing illusions.\NWhat it should say is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.41,0:19:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,how you see them\Nare merely passing illusions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.49,0:19:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,created by the ego\Nto keep itself separate from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.33,0:19:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never agreed that the ego,\Nthe ego does these things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,merely to keep itself separate from God.\NThe ego does itself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.48,0:19:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the biologic nature of the ego.\NCan I have your arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.32,0:19:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego does that\Nbecause that's its biologic nature, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.80,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't know anything about God,\Nso how could it do what it does
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to keep itself separate from God\Nwhen it doesn't even know anything about God?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a presumption\Nwhich I've never agreed with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.05,0:20:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's part of the course of miracles, too.\NAnyway, I've never agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with it\Nbecause, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.32,0:20:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have to know the answer\Nto the whole conundrum
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to have created the conundrum.\NYou would have to know about God
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.05,0:20:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep yourself separate from God,\Nand if you knew about God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.57,0:20:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then you wouldn't be just a secularist,\Nso you see it's a self-defeating conundrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.90,0:20:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact\Nthat the ego does
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.06,0:20:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then maintain\Nits separation from God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but not,\Nnot because that's its purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but because that's the consequent of a fallacy,\Nbut its purpose is not the fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallacy is a fallacy\Nbecause it's a fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.01,0:21:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you'd have to know the answer of it\Nto deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.55,0:21:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.23,0:21:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Human life is an expression of God's will\Nby which the Godhead fulfills
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.39,0:21:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the actualization of infinite potentiality,\Ncalibrates at 560.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.72,0:21:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is,\Nis,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.84,0:21:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is\Nis not only created by God,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.18,0:21:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all that is,\Nis God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is,\Nis God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.46,0:21:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How it is perceived, then,\Nwould be a positionality,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's reality.\NSo we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic divinity of all things\Nshines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.97,0:21:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When the ego collapses,\Nthe radiance of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.68,0:21:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,shines as the essence of all that exists\Nshines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.74,0:21:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like a blinding light.\NYou almost step back from it like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.86,0:21:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because suddenly the awareness opens up to you\Nand you have to pull your car over
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.69,0:22:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the side of the road.\NThe intrinsic beauty and perfection
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.61,0:22:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.\NYou say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.04,0:22:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly this box of Kleenex\Ncannot be an example of divine perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.34,0:22:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this divine perfection?\NWalgreens?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.90,0:22:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmarts.\NOh, Walmarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.24,0:22:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's different.\NHa, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.08,0:22:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What strikes you at first\Nwhen this phenomena begins to unveil itself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.52,0:22:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is the stunning realization\Nthat it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.82,0:22:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That it is.\NThat anything is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.25,0:22:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the stunning realization of existence.\NTo exist as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.26,0:22:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or exist as this,\Nor exist as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.49,0:23:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really make that much difference.\NLike, these are flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.24,0:23:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are flowers,\Nand these are flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.76,0:23:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What's stunning is that they exist at all.\NThat anything has existence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.97,0:23:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is the first stunning thing.\NSo, as I look at these flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let myself look at them too long\Nbecause the divinity of their beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.06,0:23:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to shine forth\Nand you end up,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.49,0:23:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop talking\Nbecause you're, like,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.61,0:23:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to speak at the splendor\Nof the revelation of such incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.44,0:23:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, after a certain degree\Nof divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.40,0:23:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a development of inner awareness,\Nyou go past a certain stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.76,0:23:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to function in the world,\Nyou have to pull back to a certain degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.94,0:23:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the state that you were driving\Naround the side of the mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.08,0:23:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't, you know,\Ndrive into the city
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.26,0:23:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and drive through Phoenix\Nin that particular level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.79,0:24:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to get off the road.\NSo, these states of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to come\Nand then they recede
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.79,0:24:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because if they continue,\Nit's almost impossible to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.72,0:24:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In a state of divine illumination,\Nit's almost impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.40,0:24:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to function in the world.\NIn fact, it is impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.25,0:24:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to function in the world.\NIn fact, it's hard to even stay in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.45,0:24:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because in that level,\Nyou have permission to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.89,0:24:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see you're not a physical body,\Nso you're not going to die anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.57,0:24:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you depart\Nfrom the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.70,0:24:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NHuman life is an expression of God's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.43,0:24:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an expression of God's will\Nby which the Godhead fulfills
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.25,0:24:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the actualization of infinite potentiality.\NThe infinite potentiality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.43,0:24:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be anything and everything.\NTo be a flower
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.90,0:25:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or to be a thing that you wave in the air.\NI like this next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.30,0:25:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fun one.\NMan descended from the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.02,0:25:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and fell from the heavens.\NHa, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.12,0:25:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh.\NHa, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.08,0:25:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Man fell from the stars\Nand descended from the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.58,0:25:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a descent.\NAnd then we have the next one,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.26,0:25:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwinian biologic certitude\Nthat man descended from the monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.49,0:25:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Man descended from the monkeys.\NAh, poor monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.01,0:25:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They always got to blame for it.\NHa, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.17,0:25:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A monkey once said to me,\Ndon't blame me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.31,0:25:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.\NDon't blame me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.13,0:25:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a monkey.\NI had a monkey for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.69,0:25:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was funny.\NA macaque monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.54,0:25:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also had a kinkajou.\NA kinkajou is a South American honey bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.36,0:26:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I lived alone then.\NAnd so I got this kinkajou.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.96,0:26:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the kinkajou is a South American honey bear\Nwith a long tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.71,0:26:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And he hung on a cage over my bathtub.\NAnd I would be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.17,0:26:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget whether I was going to school\Nor working, what I was doing then.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.74,0:26:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, and the kinkajou\Nwas sort of,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.58,0:26:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,his fur got more dull.\NAnd his eyes didn't have the shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.76,0:26:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he sort of lost his appetite quite a bit.\NJust sort of lethargic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.72,0:26:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought,\Nwell, he's lonely probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.86,0:26:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it is.\NSo I went out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.90,0:26:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I bought him a macaque monkey.\NSo I got him a monkey for a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.14,0:26:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the monkey hung in a cage\Non another big hook over the bathtub.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.22,0:26:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was the macaque monkey\Nand here was the kinkajou.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.79,0:26:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the monkey didn't like the kinkajou at all.\NAnd would start throwing things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.57,0:26:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at the kinkajou.\NAnything he could get hold of,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.48,0:26:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he would throw it.\NThrow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.68,0:27:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the kinkajou instantly came to life.\NHis fur got nice and shiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.58,0:27:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And his eyes were bright.\NAnd he was very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.54,0:27:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess, right,\Nhe missed companionship.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.44,0:27:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one day,\Nto finish the stories on the kinkajou,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.18,0:27:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinkajou is a South American honey bear.\NAnd he's got a long tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.60,0:27:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're friendly and nice and fun.\NAnd they climb all over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.88,0:27:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I didn't know it,\Nbut they're basically alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.12,0:27:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So those were my drinking days.\NI had a bottle of whiskey,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.27,0:27:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a decanter with wine or whiskey,\NI forget,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.09,0:27:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting in the window.\NAnd one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.85,0:27:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he got the lock off his cage\Nand he got out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.03,0:27:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I came home,\Nhe was laying on the floor drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.21,0:28:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked him up in the encyclopedia\Nand various things,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.89,0:28:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it said that they are naturally alcoholic.\NAnd they will find fermented fruit
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.50,0:28:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and get drunk on it.\NSo they grow in the jungle
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.10,0:28:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's fermented bananas\Nand they get kooked on bananas
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.88,0:28:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and then kooked on the next thing.\NSo anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.22,0:28:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,he got drunk and I came over.\NHe was just passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.69,0:28:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I picked him up\Nand put him back in his cage
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.53,0:28:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and he slowly came back with a hangover.\NFunny thing about six,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.13,0:28:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,nine months later,\Nhe got out of the cage again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.77,0:28:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kinkajou figured out\Nhow to open the cage again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.77,0:28:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I got home,\Nhe was lying on the carpet drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.00,0:28:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he was lying,\Nno, he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.24,0:28:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he had knocked the bottle,\Nthe decanter over
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.12,0:28:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had the whiskey in before\Nwas now empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.90,0:28:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But he'd gone over\Nand knocked over that decanter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.15,0:28:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was going right back\Nto where he'd gotten the whiskey before
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.93,0:29:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and knocked the decanter over.\NHe had a decanter rope only.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.08,0:29:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This time there wasn't any in it,\Nso he wasn't drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.02,0:29:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought it was so interesting\Nhow one life form
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.06,0:29:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,energizes another life form\Njust by virtue of their existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.00,0:29:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,just by virtue of the fact that we are.\NSo one of the,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.24,0:29:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you say,\Nwhat good am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.46,0:29:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What good can I serve the world?\NOf what worth am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.44,0:29:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The first worth you have\Nis that you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.22,0:29:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NIs that nice to think of?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.20,0:29:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody agrees,\Nnice to realize that you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.77,0:29:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here doesn't want to be?\NIt's nice that everybody wants to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.03,0:29:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice because you already are.\NYou see how screwed up you'd,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.84,0:30:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be if you didn't want to be\Nand you actually you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.76,0:30:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, later on you could look back\Nand say, well, at least I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.23,0:30:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the next thing,\Ncan I ask our nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.31,0:30:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at least I will be again.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.19,0:30:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The world and earthly life\Nare the optimum avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.69,0:30:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For the evolution of consciousness\Nand human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.58,0:30:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,From its animal origins\Nto its spiritual enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.32,0:30:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and salvation.\NMan is therefore the crossover
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.45,0:30:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from the animal to the angelic.\NSo it says,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.65,0:30:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,although it's true,\Nit's not a truth of a highest nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.61,0:30:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only 255.\NThe world and its human life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.92,0:30:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,are only one dimension of existence\Namong many other possible dimensions
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.26,0:30:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's 450.\NSo you can see that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.74,0:31:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a degree then of election.\NEach one of us has elected.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.48,0:31:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's verify that.\NWe never verified that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.69,0:31:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us has elected\Nto choose this human existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.25,0:31:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us is elected.\NWe've chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.37,0:31:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NEach one of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.81,0:31:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,our own free will has chosen to be here.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.93,0:31:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye alibis.\NAlibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.11,0:31:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us may not remember it.\NWe don't remember that moment
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.56,0:31:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual evolution\Nthat we agreed and chose to reincarnate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.38,0:31:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay with everybody?\NAnybody protest?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.02,0:31:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No protesters?\NUnfair to humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.64,0:31:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like,\Nwhatever happens on this planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.32,0:32:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there's always protesters.\NGod bless the protesters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.36,0:32:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a certain,\Naliveness to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.32,0:32:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a carnival for goodness\Nand giving away free money,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.47,0:32:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd be protesters.\NThere's always protesters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.67,0:32:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I never go to a peace meeting\Nbecause of the protesters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.67,0:32:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so violent that I'm afraid to go to them.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.15,0:32:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The world represents the fusion\Nof the linear and the nonlinear
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.77,0:32:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the actuality exists\Noutside the domain of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.78,0:32:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and causality.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.45,0:32:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were sort of saying that before.\NCausality is a projection
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.04,0:32:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from the human mind.\NEverything is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.65,0:32:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomously and spontaneously,\Nand nothing is being caused
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.62,0:33:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by anything else.\NWhat's happening is potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.24,0:33:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests as actuality.\NSo the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.04,0:33:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of everyone in this room\Nis to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.96,0:33:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality.\NFor everyone in this room
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.98,0:33:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is enlightenment.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.99,0:33:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No excuses.\NEveryone has chosen to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.26,0:33:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next time you feel down\Nand discouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.38,0:33:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything is going wrong,\Nyou ask yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.55,0:33:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,now why did I choose to be here then?\NIf everything is so screwed up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.69,0:33:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm so hopeless\Nand the world is so screwed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.79,0:33:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,why am I here?\NWhy am I here?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.57,0:33:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To ask yourself that periodically\Nis the basis of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.23,0:33:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the basis of wisdom?\NWhat is the meaning of my existence?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.45,0:33:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the truth of my existence\Nto the degree that I can know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.35,0:34:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one day comes an understanding.\NBut the understanding is nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.68,0:34:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an awareness of how\Nthat which could have been is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.56,0:34:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, that which is\Noriginates that which could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.34,0:34:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a one-way street.\NIt goes in both.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.82,0:34:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes in both ways.\NIt goes in both directions simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.06,0:34:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The world offers the gift of life itself\Nvia beingness and existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.66,0:34:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,whereby consciousness is made experiential\Nand thus reified as the ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.89,0:34:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arises a capacity\Nfor existence awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.16,0:34:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that is a mouthful.\NWhat in the world does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.92,0:35:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It means we're here.\NWe're here to discover the spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.18,0:35:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,behind our sense of existence\Nand discover that it is the reality of God
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.17,0:35:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that has become manifest\Nand that it's experienced as the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.84,0:35:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the self with a small s.\NThat's the one that we beat ourself up about.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.42,0:35:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's the self with a large s.\NThe infinite self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.68,0:35:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of consciousness itself.\NConsciousness doesn't identify in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.60,0:35:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,does not identify itself as separate\Nor an individual in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.56,0:35:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the human, the introduction of the humanness\Nthat makes the mind assume that that which is is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.54,0:36:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is is called me.\NAnd I've given you the story of the cat before.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.65,0:36:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the story about the cat.\NAnd you tell the cat, the cat says, who am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.02,0:36:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you tell him, you're a cat.\NHow many of you have heard this story before?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.97,0:36:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, anyway, the cat's, you tell,\NI can't see anything out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.71,0:36:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so I presume some ants went up.\NSo you tell the cat what a cat is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.25,0:36:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get the encyclopedia\Nand you read them all four or five pages on the feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.15,0:36:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get a little bit of a sense of who's a cat.\NThe cat says, I don't know why this story is going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.00,0:36:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And you help me find animal world, et cetera.\NAnd the cat listens respectfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.56,0:36:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then at the end he says, but that's not who I am.\NAnd you say, well who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.03,0:36:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cat says, I'm just me.\NThe thing I like about the story
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.21,0:37:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is it crystallizes all of this into sort of a comical story.\NThat what each one of us really experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.47,0:37:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you're experiencing is that you're experiencing.\NWhat you're experiencing of is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.68,0:37:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're experiencing your hand here or your hand there,\Nor this is a Kleenex box, that's all irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.21,0:37:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's of interest and what's significant in value\Nis that you're experiencing, period, that you are experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.10,0:37:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, by reductionism, you can get back to the point\Nthat which I am is not different than experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.26,0:37:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, that which I am, in reality,\Nis always experiencing and experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.29,0:37:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You experienced it that way when I was a kid.\NYou experienced it that way when I was rich, when I was poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.05,0:38:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was sick, I was well.\NThat which you are is experiences your own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.67,0:38:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To experience your own existence.\NEventually, we say, how do I experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.34,0:38:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience that I experience.\NHow can I know that I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.72,0:38:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual reality of the self is due to the reality of God.\NExperienced as the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.60,0:38:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,God imminent.\NSo it's because of the self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.66,0:38:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that the self with a small s presumes that it is me.\NIt is because of the presence of God within.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.75,0:38:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Were it not for the presence of God within,\Nyou would not have consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.19,0:38:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Without consciousness, you would not know that you are.\NEveryone presumes that their consciousness is innate to their existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.86,0:39:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone presumes that everyone knows that they are.\NMany things are, but don't know that they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.77,0:39:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.\NMany things are, but do not know that they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.59,0:39:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there are many humans who are,\Nbut are not conscious that they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.68,0:39:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That would always be fuddled with people.\NPeople would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.06,0:39:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how can that be?\NHow can you be and not know that you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.69,0:39:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they are without being aware of their own existence as existence.\NThat's a lower level of consciousness, below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.64,0:39:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They are, but are not aware that they are.\NIf you look at it, you can understand that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.20,0:40:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All contextualizations of the world are conjectural orientations\Nas life is lived solely by subjective experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.92,0:40:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NTo a certain extent, 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.77,0:40:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It means it's true.\NIt's not overwhelmingly true.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.93,0:40:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not spiritually true.\NWhat is the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.20,0:40:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Man is just a highly evolved hominid,\Nand therefore merely a biologic species and genus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.74,0:40:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And spirituality is a product of imagination.\NThat's about 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.48,0:40:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All spirit.\NThe Skeptic's Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.34,0:40:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the Skeptic's?\NWhat do they write?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.28,0:40:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Skeptic's Bible?\NIs that the name of that book?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.77,0:40:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The Skeptic's Dictionary.\NThe Skeptic's Dictionary, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.05,0:40:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe Skeptic's Dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.05,0:40:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Gallup reads about 160 or 170.\NAnd that's the kind of where they come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.96,0:40:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Merely a biologic spirituality is a product of imagination.\NThat's a very interesting book
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.56,0:41:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because everything that is spiritual gets ridiculed in that particular book.\NBecause from that particular book,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.40,0:41:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,only pedestrians,\Nand physicality is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.67,0:41:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And anything beyond the most mundane consciousness level 170 or so is unreal.\NMan is an environmental disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.60,0:41:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And the sooner he self-destructs and returns the world to nature,\Nthe better.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.90,0:41:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw that this morning on television.\NThis is the sort of crazy environmentalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.85,0:41:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The crazy environmentalist is worried about,\Nthis morning on TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.99,0:41:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,was worried about,\Nthe sheep in New Zealand are belching and passing intestinal gas
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.63,0:41:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and emitting methane into the environment.\NSo help me God, this is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.56,0:42:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The environmentalist says we should all become vegetarians\Nbecause to eat animals, you got to have animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.10,0:42:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the animals pass gas.\NI could laugh into a vulgar joke right now, but I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.28,0:42:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That was this morning's television, right?\NEnvironmentalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.67,0:42:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheep are belching.\NThey said belching.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.78,0:42:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Or come out the other end, he said.\NSo anyway, either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.64,0:42:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Contaminating the environment with methane.\NSo these people think that the environment is God
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.14,0:42:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that God is vulnerable.\NSo anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.52,0:43:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the extremes to which people can go are really quite interesting.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.28,0:43:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some people who say,\NI forget what they're in India.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.48,0:43:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they put a cloth over their face\Nso that they won't accidentally inhale bacteria
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.78,0:43:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby kill the bacteria.\NThey do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.20,0:43:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They wear a thing over their face so they won't inhale bacteria\Nbecause they don't want to harm the bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.67,0:43:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are people that have not accepted something within themselves\Nthat is profoundly human, humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.35,0:43:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, human.\NAnd they have demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.26,0:43:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They've demonized it.\NThey've demonized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.68,0:43:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what in psychiatry is called a reaction formation.\NThe fact that you are so far over on this side
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.61,0:43:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,means that you're really over on the other side, you see.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.83,0:43:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Man is just a highly evolved hominid\Nand therefore merely a biologic species
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.07,0:44:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirituality is a product of imagination.\NThat is a current political positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.82,0:44:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner he self-destructs and returns to worldliness,\Nthe nature, the better, calibrates at 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.36,0:44:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind is on a learning curve of biologic social evolution,\Ncalibrates at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.27,0:44:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're on a learning curve.\NWe're on a learning curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.19,0:44:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would explain many of the phenomena.\NWe can certainly see different regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.71,0:44:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate the different regions of the world\Nand the different countries in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.75,0:44:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see extreme, extreme differences.\NThere are whole...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.81,0:44:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,huge sections of the world\Nthat live at consciousness level 160, 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.82,0:44:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They live by death and terrorism\Nand beheading people and torture
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.98,0:44:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and belittling of children, women and animals, etc.\NThen you live...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.82,0:45:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then there are people that live on the highest level.\NThey wish no harm to any living being
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.00,0:45:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are benign in their viewpoint.\NSo meaning is a semantic linguistic construction
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.05,0:45:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,where no one has the right to say,\Nwell, I'm a person, I'm a person,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.94,0:45:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not a person.\NSo we live in a very coherent reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.04,0:45:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, any and all statements are equally valid\Nas part of the current political collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.16,0:45:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the intellectual basis of the country.\NIt is...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.24,0:45:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning is more than just a semantic,\Nalthough it is on a superficial level,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.64,0:45:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,something that can be superimposed.\NMeaning radiates forth when you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.05,0:45:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,can differentiate appearance from essence.\NWhen you can see the difference between...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.83,0:45:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and essence meaning shines forth from the essence so it differentiates\Nperception perception is what you think a thing is from essence so all the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.78,0:46:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness work we've done really constantly approaches the same question\Nit what is the difference between the essence of this and its appearance so
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.31,0:46:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness calibration cuts through appearance and what we calibrate is\Nessence because we can't all of us discern the wolf in the sheep's clothing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.77,0:46:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore consciousness calibration is incredibly unique it's the first time\Nactually in man's history other than by divine revelation that man has had the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.89,0:46:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to discern truth the essence of truth from falsehood that is a fact that\Nis a fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.66,0:46:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is a fact that\Nis a fact that so I have great respect for it it's like you've you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.24,0:46:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so I have great respect for it it's like you've you\Nso I have great respect for it it's like you've you accidentally fell into something of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.16,0:47:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,accidentally fell into something of\Naccidentally fell into something of profound significance and application
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.40,0:47:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,profound significance and application\Nprofound significance and application which the world doesn't even know about
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.22,0:47:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which the world doesn't even know about\Nwhich the world doesn't even know about and which the majority of the people in
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.76,0:47:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and which the majority of the people in\Nand which the majority of the people in the world wouldn't begin to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.58,0:47:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the world wouldn't begin to understand\Nthe world wouldn't begin to understand even if you explained it to him need to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.28,0:47:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you explained it to him need to\Neven if you explained it to him need to tell me without even going to where's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.23,0:47:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me without even going to where's\Nis that place in Cuba? Yes. Without even going there, I can look at the name or a picture of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.17,0:47:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody. I can ask specific questions, where he was, what he did, what he decided, what he said,\Nwhat he said yes to, who he served, and what his intentions are when he leaves. I can know it was
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.16,0:48:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,certitude. What he tells the questioner could be anything that comes into his mind that he thinks\Nthe questioner will fall for. But what he's really up to, what he's really up to, she doesn't even
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.52,0:48:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,have to know. I hold this guy's picture in mind. I say the person I'm picturing in my mind\Ncalibrates under 200. The person I picture in my mind calibrates under 200. He wishes no good to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.87,0:48:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States of America. Resist. He will commit violence the minute he gets a chance to.\NResist. He feels that's his
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.71,0:48:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual demand. He's planning on killing right now. He's going to kill as soon as he can.\NAll right. How safe is that person to release that I just looked at? He doesn't even know I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.60,0:49:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at him. I got the truth of him. Sometimes even more than the person will acknowledge to\Nthemselves. Without touching him, without torturing him, without waterboarding him,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.10,0:49:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,without threatening him, without impairing his legal rights,\NI already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.56,0:49:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what he's up to. All I have to do is calibrate him. I can do the same with an animal in the zoo.\NI can say this Komodo dragon calibrates that. What does the Komodo dragon calibrate? 160?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.50,0:49:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think 160. My old friend the Komodo dragon. You see, the Komodo dragon is not evil. He's not evil.\NHe's just being what he is. One bite from a Komodo dragon and your death is certain. It's only a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.83,0:49:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,matter of time.\NThat's because of what he is. So the Komodo dragon is not evil. He takes a bite out of you and then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.89,0:50:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he follows you for a couple days because one bite from a Komodo dragon has so many incredible\Nbacteria in it that your death is certain. One bite from a Komodo dragon and you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.68,0:50:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He waits. It takes four or five days for those bacteria. But then eventually the animal falls\Nover and now he has his meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.50,0:50:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because he's evil. That's just his nature. So to be able to discern truth from falsehood\Nis extremely sophisticated and extremely rare. Yes? How much time have you got? How much time
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.89,0:50:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,have I got left? What? Oh, thank you. One minute. That's all I want to know. Uno. Uno minuto.\NI have invented the world I see. There is no, therefore, there is no point in trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.55,0:51:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,save the world for the world you see does not even exist. What you think the world is,\Nthe world is actually an opportune place for redemption and salvation. So what the world is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.08,0:51:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,really calibrates very close to 600. What you see is only in the 300s. And if you calibrate lower,\Nwhat you will see is a world that's intrinsically evil. So there are two confusing things in the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.94,0:51:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible.\NOne is evil is in the eye of Jesus Christ. Evil is in the eye of the beholder. Condemn not. Don't
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.35,0:51:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,stone the woman because what you see is in the eye of the beholder. And the seeming contradiction\Nis in the Lord's fray. And you then say, and lead us not into evil. Should it be lead us not into
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.96,0:52:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,evil? Don't describe evil because evil is a projection of your own eye. To answer that riddle\Nwill keep you busy next 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.46,0:53:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,20, 30 years. So we'll break for lunch and resume at what time? We'll, we'll come back at two o'clock\Nand avoid evil during lunch. Gloria in excelsis Deo. Praise be to thee, O Lord, most high. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.04,0:53:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed for all of us. You don't have to pray now.\NYeah. Now we're going to resume where we left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.70,0:53:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NTell them about my drunken kitty. You want to hear about my drunken kitty?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.32,0:53:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was, I think in medical school and didn't have any money. I lived in public housing.\NAnyway, it was $20, $15 a month rent, but you weren't allowed to have any pets. But I had a cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.59,0:53:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,male cat. So I thought, Jesus, what am I going to do? So I smuggled the cat in. Well,\Nhe started caterwauling around like a male cat will, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.50,0:53:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Meow, meow.\NJesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.24,0:54:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to hear it. So what'll I do? I'll sedate him. Ah.\NSo the cheapest was potassium bromide, you know, and bromo-seltzer. The sedative is potassium
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.63,0:54:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,bromide. So I got some potassium bromide and I salted his breakfast food a little bit with it.\NWhen I got home from school that day and I walked into the apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.58,0:54:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,he came walking across like this. He went, meow, meow.\NPurring up a storm. Meow, meow, purring. And then he fell over on his side. Plunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.33,0:55:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And he just lay there purring. Didn't even want to get up.\NSo that's my drunken kitty story. It's funny because it was true anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.74,0:55:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was so happy and content to just be, he was just stoned, you know, just fell over.\NOh lordy. Let's see, where were we? 31. Yes, one's perception of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.93,0:55:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pretty obvious to you now. One's perception of the world is consequent\Nto the observer's level of consciousness. And at a certain point you see the beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.56,0:55:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the divinity of everything that exists. At lower levels, everything looks ugly.\Nand things are looked at utilitarian
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.65,0:55:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a certain level\Neverybody wants to know
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.71,0:55:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,how much is this worth?\NYou've seen people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.91,0:55:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing in their mind is money.\NHow much is this worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.29,0:55:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How much could I sell this for?\NHow much could I get for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.09,0:56:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How much is your soul?\NOh, okay, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.34,0:56:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOne's perception of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.52,0:56:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is consequent\Nto your own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.04,0:56:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So Nisargadatta Maharaj\Nwhen he said
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.12,0:56:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in worrying\Nabout the world you see
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.20,0:56:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world you see\Ndoesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.42,0:56:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But what he means by that\Nis you don't see the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.38,0:56:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You only see what you project out there.\NAnd if you look out there
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.40,0:56:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that everyone has\Nall the resources they need
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.33,0:56:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive at whatever\Ntheir level of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.92,0:56:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then at a certain level\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.96,0:56:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes very little to survive.\NIt takes very little
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.90,0:56:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive.\NIt takes very little to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.66,0:56:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because your needs\Nare very, very minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.93,0:56:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Your needs are very minimal.\NAnd the human world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.04,0:57:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is a spiritual hospital\Nand rehab unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.94,0:57:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a pretty easy one to accept,\Nisn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.34,0:57:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.\NThe human world
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.82,0:57:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is a spiritual hospital\Nand rehab unit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.54,0:57:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's here for rehab.\NAnd karma is God's own
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.62,0:57:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,bailout plan and rescue package.\NCalibrates, we said that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.90,0:57:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,like for a joke,\Nbut it does calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.04,0:57:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,around 350.\NIt is God's own bailout plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.34,0:57:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And divine intention\Nis that we have a chance
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.18,0:57:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo the negative\Nand create positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.80,0:57:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Undo negative karma\Nand create positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.07,0:57:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have permission\Nto ask what I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.58,0:57:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, everyone has had a,\Nyou know, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.15,0:58:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of people here\Nhave had a previous
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.39,0:58:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,human existence resist.\NMost of the people here
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.22,0:58:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have been here a number of times.\NThe average number is over four,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.98,0:58:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,six, seven.\NThe average person has had
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.02,0:58:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,six previous human lifetimes\Nthat you don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.42,0:58:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in an altered state\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.60,0:58:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you can remember them.\NPast life, recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.57,0:58:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There are very specific\Ntechniques of past life recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.83,0:58:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, the Whatchamacallit Institute\Nin the east of Virginia.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.25,0:58:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NMonroe Institute teaches one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.32,0:58:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've got people locally\Nthat do past life regression.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.04,0:58:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And in altered states\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.46,0:58:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hypnosis is very simple.\NSelf-hypnosis,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.43,0:58:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you just picture yourself\Ngoing down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.57,0:58:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You count yourself down.\NAnd when you get to the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.82,0:58:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, the door will open\Nand I will,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.24,0:59:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,emerge back into that\Nlifetime. And you open
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.78,0:59:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the door and you walk in and that lifetime\Njust resumes. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.12,0:59:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,like the start of a film and the end of a\Nfilm. It just
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.72,0:59:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,resumes. It resumes.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.16,0:59:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to just be aware that\Nthis is not your first and only time here
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.13,0:59:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of course that's helpful because\Nif you screw it up you can come back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.95,0:59:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This time you just\Ndon't bet on the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.35,0:59:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a friend. First he got off\Nalcohol. Then he got on to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.09,0:59:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,pills. Then he got\Non to gambling. Then he
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.23,0:59:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,got on to women.\NIt was one
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.13,0:59:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,addiction after another.\NAnd it's a good thing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.21,0:59:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he wasn't really into eating or he'd weigh about\N400 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.95,0:59:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what he did\Nhe had to do it to an excess degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.25,1:00:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nthis is a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.04,1:00:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,hospital and rehab unit. It has a\Ncertain reality because it calibrates over
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.18,1:00:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,200.\N265.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.44,1:00:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the one\Nwe said was a joke. God's own bailout
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.88,1:00:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,plan and rescue package\Nhas a reality. It's 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.76,1:00:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course that's what the Buddha teaches.\NSo we've
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.32,1:00:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated\Na basic Buddhic belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.44,1:00:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity doesn't teach that.\NChristianity comes from a different direction
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.98,1:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't get into the whole\Nsubject of karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.62,1:00:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It just has no opinion about it. It doesn't say\Nyes or no. It just
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.26,1:00:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,ignores it.\NThe world is getting hotter due to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.10,1:00:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,human causes is 105.\NSo we
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.48,1:00:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to worry about\Nsheep gas,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.92,1:01:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,moose gas,\Nelephant gas.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.10,1:01:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is not getting\Nhotter due to human causes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.46,1:01:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we wrote about that\Nand spoken about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.02,1:01:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth's temperature\Nice ages
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.94,1:01:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,are due to\Nthe sun's spot
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.40,1:01:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,activity on the surface of the sun.\NThe magnetic activity of the surface
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.26,1:01:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sun. And of course\Ngoing down
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.40,1:01:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,through the ice\Ngoing down through the ice you can go to the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.18,1:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,going down through the ice you can go to the sun.\Ngoing down through the ice you can go to the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.28,1:01:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go through 10,000, 20,000\Ndown to 30,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.18,1:01:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the\Nearth's temperature is related
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.49,1:01:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to the sun's spot activity\Nof the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.83,1:01:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now I think the sun's spot\Nactivity has decreased.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.25,1:01:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask. The sun's spot\Nactivity right now has decreased.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.89,1:01:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. We are not\Ngoing into a hot period. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.66,1:02:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not going into a hot period.\NSo all that is hogwash
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.52,1:02:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nand other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.50,1:02:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The human world is a spiritual hospital rehab unit.\NAs you can see one thing is how to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.22,1:02:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So partly what we've discovered in our own research\Nis one of the reasons we came back here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.70,1:02:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There is possible to discern truth from falsehood\Nand that you have within yourself the capacity.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.06,1:02:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The world won't end on 12, 21, 2012.\NOh that's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.40,1:02:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I ask people, why are you worried about that?\NThey always say, because of the, what do you call the calendar?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.74,1:02:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the Mayan calendar.\NI say, well, if you're a Mayan, worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.66,1:03:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That only applies to Mayans.\NAnd if you're not a Mayan, forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.34,1:03:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said before, if I'm wrong, I'll give you a million dollars.\NWhat in the world? What is the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.82,1:03:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one.\NWith the removal of perception, in other words, when you stop projecting out,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.85,1:03:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the world as it is,\Nthe radiance of divinity shines forth as the exquisite beauty and perfection of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.23,1:03:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the first time I saw that,\Nbecause I had surrendered everything to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.75,1:03:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and was in a high and very,\Nvery rarefied space.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.32,1:04:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly anybody had ever been there.\NI saw a few people had been there over the ages.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.06,1:04:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it dawned on me that I had surrendered everything to God,\Nbut I had not surrendered life to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.30,1:04:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NSo I surrendered everything, all that I have, all that I have been,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.52,1:04:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all I believe, everything I could say about myself.\NAnd then I said, this too,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.15,1:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrender to Thee, O Lord, and I laid down my life to God.\NAnd, as I've described before,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.89,1:04:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,there were a few moments of very intense agony,\Nextreme agony, as I felt myself dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.22,1:04:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was dying. That which I had been died.\NAnd then, suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.50,1:05:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the door opened up, and the exquisite perfection and the radiance of divinity shone forth.\NIt was like blinding.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.30,1:05:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the beauty is so stunning, it just knocks your back on your feet.\NThe radiance, the divinity, the perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.56,1:05:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In ordinary life, we blind ourself to it for,\Nbecause for one thing, you can't really function in that state.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.66,1:05:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't.\NI didn't function for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.16,1:05:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't function for years, even.\NAnd, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.16,1:05:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you, when, by revelation, one sees\Nthe true reality of, of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.68,1:05:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the exquisite perfection of all that exists,\Nis due to the fact that all that exists is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.94,1:05:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that you see here is an expression of divinity.\NDivinity as this table. Divinity as this paper Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.54,1:06:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity as this soda bottle. Divinity as this pointer.\NDivinity as the coffee. Divinity as Susie.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.70,1:06:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see divinity as me?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.40,1:06:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You better.\NYou see the perfection. You become aware of the perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.85,1:06:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because you let go of judgmentalism.\NYou don't process anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.51,1:06:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, one part of consciousness is the processor.\NIt doesn't just see a thing. It instantly processes it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.01,1:06:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That processing happens in one ten-thousandth of a second.\NAnd it's very hard to get ahead of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.83,1:06:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In a high meditative state, you can suddenly cross.\NSee things as they are before the processor gets to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.22,1:06:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The processor comes in one ten-thousandth of a second\Nand edits everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.25,1:07:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As it's perceived, it's edited as fast as you perceive it.\NTherefore, in ordinary life, what you're constantly witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.88,1:07:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is what your consciousness has processed.\NYou're not seeing what is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.97,1:07:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're seeing what has been processed in one ten-thousandth of a second.\NIt's been interpreted, labeled, given a name, made right or wrong, pro and con, anti.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.36,1:07:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In one instant, one can catch it, however.\NAnd I've told before, the time I caught it, when a rabbit ran in front of the car,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.58,1:07:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and just as the rabbit ran in front of the car, my foot pushed down on the brake\Nand stopped the car, brought the car down.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.92,1:08:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I caught that I did it before I thought of doing it.\NAnd I caught the ego trying to take credit for saving the rabbit's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.14,1:08:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the foot went down and slowed and saved the rabbit's life.\NAnd then the ego jumped in one ten-thousandth of a second and claimed credit.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.27,1:08:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the higher meditative states, what happens is you eventually cross over\Nthe processor.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.41,1:08:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see everything as it is, not as it has been processed.\NBelief systems are so powerful, they're like a television set.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.73,1:08:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They interpret and process everything.\NYou see nothing as it is on television because everything, the angle has been selected,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.95,1:08:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the lighting has been selected, the sound has been selected,\Nthe verbal description has been selected, the politicalization has been selected,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.95,1:08:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the grammar has been selected.\NThousands of selections have occurred before you even get a chance to view it on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.24,1:09:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you say you saw it, you didn't really see it.\NWhat you saw was a processed interpretation of it with multiple slants.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.72,1:09:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, why they even picked this particular scene to take a picture of.\NI mean, in the selection of it, they're saying this is important,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.72,1:09:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this contains a hidden message in the visual imaging, in the soundtrack, whatever.\NSo what we see is an edited world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.32,1:09:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Within ourself is the processor, which is pretty much like a TV production studio.\NIt selects what to consider important, how to interpret it, how to feel about it, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.18,1:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NIt comes to you once in a while in a meditative state, not necessarily formal meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.50,1:09:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but a time very often when you're walking along in the woods.\NAnd not thinking about anything in particular, and all of a sudden time seems to stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.03,1:10:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole woods become silent.\NYou can hear every leaf fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.07,1:10:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's magical.\NEverybody here had experiences like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.81,1:10:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where suddenly the world is like mystically beautiful?\NEverybody?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.94,1:10:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God.\NThank you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.56,1:10:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Time comes to a stop.\NJudgementalism stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.26,1:10:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentalization stops.\NAnd now let's say the old-fashioned tape recorder,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.42,1:10:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you recorded it and then you heard it come out the other end.\NAnd that was already edited within one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.42,1:10:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the processor stops, you hear it the way it's coming into the recording machine,\Nnot how it comes out of the monitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.54,1:10:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that is a divine state.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.04,1:11:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it occurs from 600 and up.\NI think that state occurs from 600 and up, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.77,1:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that state occurs, consciousness level 600 and up,\Nwhere the internal processor stops processing information
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.02,1:11:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and just experiences it as it is,\Nwith no intervention, with no editing, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.97,1:11:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With the removal of perception, then the radiance of divinity shines forth\Nas the exquisite beauty and perfection of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.36,1:11:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrates at 645.\NSo the experience that you had, we calibrated it, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.11,1:11:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 700, like that.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.61,1:11:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you have those experiences, you're seeing the world the way it is.\NIf you can remove yourself from the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.30,1:11:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had such opportunities in past decades to leave the world\Nfor periods, prolonged periods of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.80,1:12:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have to function in the world,\Nand a divine state would take over.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.70,1:12:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you didn't have to go anywhere or do anything,\Nyou had no responsibilities,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.83,1:12:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a television set,\NI never went out or read a book,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.92,1:12:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you could stay in this divine state for prolonged periods.\NAnd such periods.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.65,1:12:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I lived by myself in a relatively large house.\NAnd as I said, I would forget there was a body
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.38,1:12:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or had any connection with the body.\NAnd when I passed a mirror, I saw somebody in the mirror,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.38,1:12:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and it scared me.\NI didn't know who was in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.38,1:12:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's someone in the house.\NAnd another time, as I've related before,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.38,1:12:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried walking through a wall,\Nand the physical body smacked right up against the wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.38,1:12:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you no longer identified\Nyourself as the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.88,1:13:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the expanded states of consciousness\Nthat we strive for with meditation, fasting,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.11,1:13:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,religious and spiritual techniques and rituals,\Nwhich we hope to increase
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.24,1:13:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by the advancement of our own level of consciousness.\NNow, is there another slide we'd have to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.40,1:13:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThat's it. Oh, good. That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.20,1:13:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where I wanted to end up.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.20,1:13:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We were going to discuss something\Nbecause we have a little time before the question and answer starts.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.78,1:13:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll ask for questions from the audience later.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.03,1:13:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Do you want this thing?\NNo. Okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.80,1:13:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, later we're going to have questions and answers from the audience.\NAnd first, we'll just have some that we've been given.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.68,1:13:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And Susan has some that she wanted to bring forth.\NIn regards to our lecture. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.66,1:14:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo, you know, in the world, but not of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.12,1:14:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, are you saying, you know, with all of us facing, you know,\Nmortgages being repossessed and the panicking of jobs being lost,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.62,1:14:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and what would you consider our approach to those everyday,\Nyou know, grocery bills going up?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.72,1:14:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you consider the approach to that\Nas a spiritual person?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.22,1:14:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we approach those challenges that are in the everyday world?\NI think by non-resistance, by acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.18,1:14:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You accept the fact that there's nothing but peanut butter and bread in the house to eat.\NSo, you got peanut butter and bread in the house to eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.06,1:14:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is your complaint?\NSo, in a purified state, you let go wanting to change anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.97,1:15:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You let everything be as it is.\NAnd then see the perfection and beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.70,1:15:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And know that God supplies all that is needed.\NAnd if something further is needed,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.71,1:15:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be provided or you will be moved to go for it.\NYou know, something and you will say,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.96,1:15:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll look in the top shelf, there might have been a box of crackers\Nand by God, there is.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.28,1:15:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBecause, you know, so many of us are facing, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.88,1:15:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,challenges as far as it goes.\NAnd it's not, it's not who we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.04,1:15:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world outside of ourselves that are producing all these challenges to us.\NSo, it's a little difficult sometimes to have faith and let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.04,1:15:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's what we perceive as challenges.\NIt's a threat to the things that we're attached to.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.07,1:16:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I'm worried about something, that means I've become attached to it.\NSo, what I do, anyway, what I do personally is I surrender my attachment to it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.05,1:16:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or my belief that I need it for happiness or for life itself. Okay?\NAnd the things that people desire and crave for are really niceties.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.69,1:16:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when it comes down to reality, to exist, you really need very little.\NI existed for months with, I had a six-pack at that Pepsi
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.14,1:16:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and a piece of cheese in the refrigerator.\NThat was it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.57,1:16:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be malnutritioned, but...\NWell, you see, that again would be judgmental and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.57,1:16:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you have malnutrition. So, big deal.\NYou get beriberi and your teeth get loose and so, let it go.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.35,1:17:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about, you know, a devoted spiritual yoga, you know, where...\NDon't forget, for years I had the opportunity to leave the world
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.50,1:17:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and do nothing but pursue a spiritual goal and direction.\NSo, I was willing to let anything go and I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.08,1:17:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of just about everything.\NEven almost let go of the physical body permanently.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.49,1:17:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then something said, well, you ought to reown it.\NYou ought to reown it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.12,1:17:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I said, well, yeah, all right.\NSo, I went back in and reowned the body again.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.62,1:17:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was perfectly happy to leave it there.\NSo, could it be our attitudes?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.12,1:17:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Our attitudes are not the best in these harder times\Nthat we're just not looking at it from the proper viewpoint then?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.12,1:17:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we try to let go our attachment and our aversion.\NOur attachments and our aversions.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.25,1:18:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And see that they're really frills.\NMost of them are frills.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.47,1:18:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying, you know, I couldn't live without a soul.\NSo and so.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.73,1:18:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could.\NOf course you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.73,1:18:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need your mittens.\NYou can keep your hands in your pockets.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.26,1:18:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you need mittens for?\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.39,1:18:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, after a while, you find out that what you actually need is very little.\NWhat you actually need is very little.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.46,1:18:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually, you cut down to whether you even need the body at all.\NAnd that's a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.96,1:18:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The times that I've had to make a decision about that.\NWere mainly in a state of bliss.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.72,1:18:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was no necessity.\NFirst of all, I'm not the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.72,1:18:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, I've experienced my own immortality.\NThat which I am has always been and always will be.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.33,1:19:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I didn't need the body for anything.\NAnd then, the fact that others needed me at that moment made me resume the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.06,1:19:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, from a very advanced point of view.\NConsciousness, spiritual position.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.25,1:19:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have released on that too.\NSo, when I was like free, you know, in a snow bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.34,1:19:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a state of bliss.\NAnd it was ten below zero, whatever it was out, blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.49,1:19:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hollowed out this space in the pile of snow by the side of the highway.\NAnd I crawled in there to get out of the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.08,1:19:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And after being in there a very short while.\NThis delicious sense of warmth and exquisite beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.08,1:19:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And the radiance of light suffused.\NAnd that which I am, I experienced as forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.29,1:20:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am has always been and will always be.\NAnd there was no need to resume the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.00,1:20:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The body was superfluous.\NIf you're eternal, what do you need a body for?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.38,1:20:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but then my father came and shook my ankle.\NHe'd followed my paper route and found me there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.06,1:20:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to make a decision.\NIf I was going to breathe and resume the body or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.06,1:20:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw that if I didn't, my father would think that he was responsible for my dying.\NSo, I couldn't allow that to happen to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.99,1:20:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there the love was an attachment, you might say.\NAnd from the highest, most advanced realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.28,1:20:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have left the body then and let him worry about his feeling of loss of self.\NIt's his problem, not mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.78,1:20:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But each time I resumed the body like that, it was always for the sake of something or someone else.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.31,1:21:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the end, love can be an attachment.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.40,1:21:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, it is not.\NBut one can also become attached about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.60,1:21:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo, actually, what we need to do is go back to basics.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.75,1:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the basics?\NWhat do, you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.78,1:21:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In essence, what do you really need to survive?\NWhat do you really need to survive?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.52,1:21:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as far as it goes, it's hard times.\NYou know, people are losing their jobs and can't find work or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.96,1:21:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the depressing news.\NBut like you, you were in the depression and you had three different jobs you were doing at one time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.96,1:21:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...\NWell, that was during the last big depression, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.96,1:21:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was sort of...\NYou know, born that way, sort of a driven self-sufficiency.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.28,1:22:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when other people can't find a job, I always have two.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.50,1:22:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I always had two jobs.\NYou know, I was a cab driver during the day and a bartender at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.17,1:22:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NAnd on the way home, I'd put a newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.67,1:22:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I always had two or three things going because that was just the vitality that I had.\NYou know, I don't take any credit for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.67,1:22:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the way I was put together in this lifetime with a certain drivenness and determination, go-go-ness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.35,1:22:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And, well, the pressure, it seems like...\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.70,1:22:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I look at people and I see that so many of them...\NTheir wants are so large.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.80,1:22:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou can't hear me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.80,1:23:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Their wants are more a lot of times than what their earnings are and, you know...\NI have to have that car and I have to...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.80,1:23:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be happy.\NAnd then I have to have this house and then I'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.80,1:23:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I have to have, you know, this pool for the house and then I'll be happy.\NBut then when they get all that, it's always another thing that they're not happy with.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.83,1:23:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat's...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.83,1:23:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The error of seeing happiness is something outside of yourself, something to be gained.\NHappiness, the value of things is purely a projection, each and every thing of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.24,1:23:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if you were starving to death in the middle of the desert, the Hope Diamond wouldn't do you much good.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.37,1:23:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So desirability then is, you know, is called glamour, the energy of glamour.\NIt's projected onto things.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.46,1:24:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We think the attractiveness is out there.\NThere's no attractiveness out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.46,1:24:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All attractiveness is in here.\NIt's because you desire that and want it and value it that it looks desirable and attractive to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.25,1:24:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pickled beets look very good to you if you like pickled beets and if you don't, they don't attract you, you know what I mean?\NSo the projection of value onto the external world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.25,1:24:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And that, of course, is the basis of materialism and the whole economy is based on wanting this and wanting that and wanting something else.\NAnd to instill such wants.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.79,1:24:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want something, you'll get programmed to wanting it.\NAnd better burial benefits.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.34,1:24:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Better burial benefits?\NThey're out to sell you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.34,1:25:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepaid funerals.\NI mean, right down to the very last thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.41,1:25:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Better coffins, you know what I mean?\NSo there's no end to programming people to wanting this.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.41,1:25:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So wanting this is the backbone of our economy.\NThe backbone of our economy is wanting this.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.41,1:25:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And when people stop wanting things, it all comes to a halt.\NBut when you let go wanting the physical, then you want the emotional and you want the spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.86,1:25:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're looking for, the world cannot provide.\NAnd you're looking for the return of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.92,1:25:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A glance of love is all that you really wanted that entire day.\NOne glance of love is enough for the entire day.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.90,1:25:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough for a week, if it's the right person.\NLike somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.90,1:25:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a glance.\NA glance.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.90,1:25:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See how powerful love is.\NJust a fleeting glance of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.90,1:26:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, your heart swells up, you feel fine, you're great.\NBut cutting off that glance of love, you look for the love and it's disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.22,1:26:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're in the throes of the bottom of the pits.\NSo you see that of all the values that are out there, love is the one that you crave the most, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.79,1:26:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live without money, you can go bankrupt.\NBut love is the one thing that we value above all else.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.79,1:26:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You had said in different lectures that you would go into a mall and you'd see two people\Nand they'd look at each other lovingly and you'd just burst into tears because you saw that love exchange.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.02,1:26:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So I understand that, but I don't know if everyone else here has that experience.\NAs you do just, you know, ordinary spiritual work, these phases come up.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.18,1:27:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the phase of the continuous miracles.\NMiracles begin to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.72,1:27:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only do they happen, but they start to become continuous, be continuous.\NAnd then the infinite power of love begins to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.30,1:27:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how infinitely loving everything is.\NAnd all that matters is love itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.65,1:27:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get to a certain state where you cry easily with love\Nbecause a glance of love and it just knocks you out because it's so overwhelmingly blissful.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.94,1:27:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get into a state of bliss, loving bliss, loving bliss.\NAnd some spiritual gurus get into the state of loving bliss and stay there.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.38,1:27:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Some stay for years.\NSome withdraw from the world and just stay in that state of loving bliss.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.45,1:27:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Loving blissfulness.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.14,1:28:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times we get questions from people that in the first book, Power vs. Force,\Nwe wrote that, you know, that there were about 12 gurus at that time that were,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.14,1:28:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they were above 700.\NAnd a lot of times people send us emails to that effect as to who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.46,1:28:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That was at that time, yeah.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.46,1:28:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so can you explain to them why we don't mention their names and why?\NWell, you know, we don't like to get into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.46,1:28:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do it anonymously.\NAnonymously.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.46,1:28:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.46,1:28:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we have permission to ask this.\NRight now, there's more than three people over 700.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.67,1:28:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Four people.\NSix people.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.12,1:28:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight people.\NWhat did I say, over 700?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.44,1:28:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.44,1:29:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more than six people over 700 right now.\NThere's more than five people over 700 right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.46,1:29:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Six people.\NYeah, I think that we've got five or six.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.66,1:29:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And mostly they live all over the world, you know.\NThere was one in Indonesia that calibrated extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.66,1:29:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I never did find out who it was, but I knew he was there.\NSo, all that it does is counterbalance the extreme negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.65,1:29:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you see, even one person at 700 counterbalances, you know, practically millions\Nthat are below 200 because the radiance from the energy field is so enormous.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.22,1:29:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And that radiance goes out through the vibration of the consciousness of the teacher, radiates\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.66,1:29:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And the student picks it up in their aura.\NThe student picks it up in their aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.79,1:30:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it stays there and may not become manifest for several lifetimes.\NBut you can pick up the aura of a very advanced teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.30,1:30:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it becomes, its full effect may not become manifest for a few more physical lifetimes.\NAnd then suddenly the radiance comes forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.30,1:30:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you pick up the aura of the teacher in just reading or videos or?\NCan you pick up the aura of the teacher in those?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.30,1:30:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been happy with the answer I get for that.\NIt's actually picked up from the physical presence of the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.01,1:30:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.01,1:30:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, what about meditating with the picture of the teacher?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.01,1:30:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.01,1:30:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditating with the picture of the teacher is almost as good as the physical presence.\NAlmost as good.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.07,1:30:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's surprising.\NOh, that's a very happy finding.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.07,1:30:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWe haven't asked that before.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.07,1:30:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we never asked it.\NBut that's traditional.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.10,1:31:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know, having incense and a picture or a statue, you're invoking the spirit of the teacher and identifying with the spirit of the teacher.\NAnd the most powerful of all is that you pick up the vibration, the frequency vibration of the aura of the teacher and you pick it up in your own aura.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.30,1:31:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it stays for lifetimes.\NWell, a lot of cultures, other cultures.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.30,1:31:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen you go into that high state, there's places you can go to be in that high state.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.30,1:31:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And here in the U.S., of course, we don't recognize a lot of the East Indian religions.\NAnd so, there's a lot of no place for people to go like that, which is very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.30,1:31:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a cultural tradition here like it is in, let's say, India.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.30,1:31:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is that why you say that we should carry that with us as a…\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.30,1:32:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As a subconscious in our mind?\NBecause you say to carry it with us kind of as contemplation rather than…
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.06,1:32:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, rather than meditation?\NThan meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.10,1:32:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I said in today's world, meditation is not to, you know, protracted meditation.\NIt really requires withdrawing from the world and going to unique places.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.74,1:32:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do to the utmost and still remain in the world?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.74,1:32:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do is you practice all the spiritual disciplines that you can and you spend a\Ngreat deal of time in contemplation rather than meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.47,1:32:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because meditation, you have to withdraw from the world.\NAnd I don't advise meditation when you're driving.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.92,1:33:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NSo, contemplation is more practical in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.94,1:33:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NExplain contemplation.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.94,1:33:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say contemplation, I want to know what you mean when you say that.\NYou say, but what is exactly do you mean when you say contemplation?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.94,1:33:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, that's kind of holding it in mind, but not in the present mind.\NIt's kind of in the back of my mind constantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.96,1:33:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do you…\NWhat's your interpretation of contemplation?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.96,1:33:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation is more, you know, like a daily word where there is a statement of a spiritual\Ntruth.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.02,1:33:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now during the day, you sort of tend to hold that in mind and keep returning to\Nit and maybe even pray about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.09,1:33:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,God, please reveal to me what is the true meaning of this and how does it apply to my\Nlife, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.09,1:33:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, contemplation is something you can do almost all the time.\NAll the time, no matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.09,1:34:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, as I'm talking to you now, there is going on within the consciousness the letting\Ngo of any desire to change anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.83,1:34:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The lighting is as it is.\NYour voice is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.83,1:34:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience is as it is.\NSo, there's the letting go of any intention to make anything different than the way it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.60,1:34:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is and to be totally accepting that the light may not be as perfect as I want it to be.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.89,1:34:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,As perfect as I want it or the question may not be phrased the way I want it or the table\Ncloth is not the color I want it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.98,1:34:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the mind is usually trying to be on top of things, change them, make them better,\Nmake them smoother.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.88,1:34:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kleenex box should be this way.\NNo, it should be this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.22,1:35:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the mind is always trying to fix things up.\NAnd as you reach a contemplative meditative state, the way things are is the way things
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.47,1:35:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,are.\NAnd if somebody says, you know, that's the end of all that is, just say, well, goodbye
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.16,1:35:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,then.\NSo, it's a little bit like acceptance too.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.16,1:35:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's profound acceptance, yes.\NYes, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.16,1:35:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That the world is the way it is and we can't change it.\NThe world is the way it is and you don't feel called upon to save the world, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.16,1:35:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't feel there.\NThey're called upon to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.58,1:35:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them, well, I was waiting for the second coming.\NI'm glad you're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.83,1:35:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's kind of like that joke that you tell about the man that's being robbed.\NIt's one of my favorites.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.34,1:35:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to tell that one.\NI don't remember that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.34,1:35:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Where he says, give you my money.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.37,1:36:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When he takes the gun out and he holds it to your head and says, it's your life or your\Nmoney.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.26,1:36:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jack Benny.\NThis is a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.26,1:36:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack Benny, yes.\NWell.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.26,1:36:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy comes up to him and he says, your money or your life?\NAnd Benny says, well, not so fast, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.26,1:36:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Like he had to think about it.\NBut also, you talk about one where someone, if a robber came up to you and held a gun
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.54,1:36:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to your head and said, you know, your money or your life, and you said, I don't have any\Nmoney.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.54,1:36:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So he would take your life.\NAnd you said, that's OK, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.54,1:36:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're not really the one doing it.\NIn other words, you're handling the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.71,1:37:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I always look at the karmic consequence and, you know, and so you do what you can\Nbecause of who you are at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.45,1:37:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothetically, you might have done otherwise, but you're not a hypothetical being.\NYou're who you are at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.48,1:37:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But you said that all fears, if you took away, all fears lead to death.\NSo any fear that we have leads to death in the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.90,1:37:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you're saying.\NIf you remove, peel off layer after layer after layer, you know, if I had no money,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.90,1:37:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I would.\NYeah, to get rid of fear altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.90,1:37:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo when you clear a stack of fear, you start with whatever fear is foremost right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.96,1:37:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And you surrender to that.\NYou're going to get old.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.99,1:37:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NYou're going to get ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.99,1:37:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou're going to lose your hearing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.99,1:37:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NYou won't be able to see anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.65,1:37:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou can't climb a ladder.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.65,1:37:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou can't drive the car because you can't see where the road is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.65,1:38:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo you keep surrendering one thing after another until finally you end up with a so what.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.90,1:38:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't go anywhere.\NPeople have to drive you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.31,1:38:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't put on your shirt.\NSo you won't wear a shirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.31,1:38:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't wear a shirt.\NTo hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.31,1:38:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a robe over yourself.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.61,1:38:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This, the surrendering comes up as a confrontation.\NIf your ideal is to be totally surrendered and released and free of all attachments or
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.83,1:38:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,aversions, then that intention will bring things directly to your attention that you\Nwere not aware of before.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.44,1:38:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll become aware of them.\NThey arise because you're attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.76,1:38:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're attached to comfort, then you have to let go of, you know, your attachment\Nto comfort.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.76,1:39:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NLast three or four nights I had to sleep with the steam kettle going in the steam pot,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.81,1:39:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,perking away and gurgling away and hopping and buzzing.\NAnd so I just had to let go of wanting to change it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.81,1:39:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to get rid of it.\NHe's talking about a vaporizer.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.66,1:39:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe's had a cold for the last three weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.70,1:39:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is about the first weekend that he hasn't been too congested.\NI said, we have to get over it before Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.70,1:39:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.70,1:39:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.70,1:39:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But, yeah, he complained about it bubbling.\NBubbling and popping and talking to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.86,1:39:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen you start getting messages from the steam kettle, you know, you're getting
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.04,1:39:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,one.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.38,1:39:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.38,1:39:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NSo all of us, when we're in the world but not of it, if we carry that in mind, that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.38,1:40:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,will take us towards the goal which most of us have of becoming enlightened and realizing\Nthat all this is happening outside of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.86,1:40:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jesus said that, you know, wear the world like a light garment.\NHe didn't say ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.70,1:40:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't say curse it.\NDon't pretend that it's all illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.70,1:40:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all illusion, but don't let it dominate your life.\NLet your spiritual principles dominate your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.21,1:40:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And what the physical world is like is of only passing and minor significance.\NThe fact that you're rich today or poor today is, you know, of interest but not decisive.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.26,1:40:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to live or die according to that.\NRich men die and poor men die.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.35,1:40:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So not to be too attached.\NNot to be too attached to anything in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.22,1:41:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And to see that desire is a projection.\NWhat makes a thing attractive is not what it looks like but what you project onto it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.11,1:41:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Gabe and I don't like red cars.\NBright red cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.88,1:41:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be driving along and I'll say, Gabe, do you see what I see?\NOh, he says, that's disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.77,1:41:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We play a game called bright red cars are vulgar and we hate them.\NWe like green cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.80,1:41:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We like blue cars.\NWe hate red cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.80,1:41:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright red cars are terrible.\NSo we pretend, you know, we play this game of having a terrible aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.93,1:41:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And Gabe will say, I'll tell you what's ahead up above.\NI said, no, no, I don't want to even hear about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.12,1:41:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a bright red pickup truck.\NOh, I said, no, no, no, don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.86,1:41:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you play the game of aversion, you see.\NSo in other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.86,1:42:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,people that have worked so hard and they have this,\Nthey finally bought this house that they thought they needed
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.14,1:42:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and to find out that, you know, they lost their job,\Nthey're not going to be able to make the mortgage and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.46,1:42:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's an attachment to a style of life.\NYes, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.46,1:42:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the attachment.\NAnd you can have them and lose them and life will go on just the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.75,1:42:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, and how long are you going to mourn it?\NYou have to mourn it until you let go of your attachment to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.23,1:42:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo you think the mourning is due to the loss.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.23,1:42:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The mourning is due to the fact that you're attached,\Nnot due to the loss, but attached to what you,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.23,1:42:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if it was your favorite fishing tackle and you dropped it in the water\Nand your favorite reel went to the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.23,1:42:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a feeling of loss that was your favorite fishing reel.\NBut it's not due to the fishing reel,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.58,1:42:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's due to your attachment to the fishing reel.\NAnd if somebody gives you a new one just like the one you lost,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.19,1:43:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you quickly recover.\NSo it's the feeling of loss of attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.06,1:43:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the attachment is really to the happiness involved with it.\NWhen I had that reel, I was happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.15,1:43:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I could be a happy fisherman.\NNow I've lost my reel.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.15,1:43:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can never be a happy fisherman again, you know.\NSo you write this whole scenario and then you grieve the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.30,1:43:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If youth is the only thing that could make you happy, you know,\Nwhere would we be?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.91,1:43:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In high school.\NI haven't been at 18.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.91,1:43:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been 18 for quite a while.\NIt's almost time for us to quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.91,1:43:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo all the things of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.91,1:43:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So what Jesus is saying is he doesn't say ignore the world.\NHe doesn't say, like some people do, pretend it doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.04,1:44:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't say pretend it doesn't matter.\NHe says allow it to matter but only lightly.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.30,1:44:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You miss it a little bit.\NYou wish you had your old fishing reel back.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.33,1:44:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But life goes right on and you're just as happy by dinner time as you would be.\NOnce in a while you get a little pang about your good old fishing reel.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.42,1:44:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But your life really goes on.\NSo to be in this world, so it means respect the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.03,1:44:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people get into spirituality and they disdain the world,\Nwhich I think is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.03,1:44:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's incorrect to put the world down and make it evil or make it physical\Nand make the world wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.83,1:44:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then to pretend that it doesn't matter and that it doesn't exist is also wrong.\NSo the thing I liked about Christ's teachings is it seemed,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.96,1:44:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, in my living it through myself,\Nto be respectful of the world, appreciate, thankful of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.50,1:44:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be in it but not of it.\NIn other words, not tied to the worldly world.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.50,1:45:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're tied to the worldly things,\Nthen you're going to be run by television advertisements around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.21,1:45:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To respect the world, appreciate the world,\Ngive thanks for its blessings,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.21,1:45:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and then have a higher purpose that takes you out of the world.\NSo whether the world is here or isn't here won't really affect you that much.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.40,1:45:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more convenience.\NI like that teaching.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.03,1:45:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wear the world like a light garment.\NAnd I think that is, it allows you to contemplate and walk about your business
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.03,1:45:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the same time not be tied into a knot.\NYou know, somebody didn't smile at you when you went to work this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.38,1:45:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she didn't even smile at me.\NI wonder what she means by that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.38,1:45:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole day is poisoned now by paranoia.\NI wonder what they meant by that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.51,1:45:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt's their problem what they meant by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.51,1:45:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what they meant by it.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.51,1:46:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NSmile at yourself in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.93,1:46:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more important than having other people smile at you.\NGive yourself a smile.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.41,1:46:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here, I pledge you to smile at yourself in the mirror next time you look there.\NEverybody agrees?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.56,1:46:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for me.\NGod bless you, George, Herbert, and Serena, Pinky, Polly, whatever your name is.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.72,1:46:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe're going to take a quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.72,1:46:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.54,1:46:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Phoenix on it.\NThere's a white van with a phoenix on it, and the custodian has your keys.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.98,1:46:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe're going to take a quick break, and then we'll resume with question and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.58,1:47:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be 15 minutes, and if you could please line up on this side for question and answers.\NWe will take question and answers and pictures at that time.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.58,1:47:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right-hand side of the auditorium, if you have any books that you need signed,\Nwe will do that also.
